Galax urceolata (Poir.) Brummitt
det. Michelle L. Gaynor (FLAS)                      2024

PLANTS OF THE CUMBERLAND PLATEAU
McCREARY COUNTY, KENTUCKY, U.S.A.

GALAX APHYLLA L.
Diapensiaceae

Fairly common and abundant on dry ground, along a
dangerously steep S-facing slope, with *Kalmia latifolia*,
*Vaccinium arboreum*, *Quercus alba*, *Q. prinoides*,
*Danthonia*, *Galax aphylla*, *Amelanchier*, *Pinus echinata*;
just S of camping area along trail basically overlooking
N side of Cumberland River, Cumberland Falls State
Resort Park, Daniel Boone National Forest; UTM
coords. approx. 16 737697E 4080251 N; elev. 1000'.

John B. Nelson 21967
with John E. Cely                                      8 VII 2001
